<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--China-CommunistParty     06-17 0111</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China-Communist Party,0112</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One In Four Accepted For Party Membership</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China has purged 153,000 people from its
Communist Party over the past five years and disciplined another
656,000 as part of a drive to improve the quality of its members,
the government announced today.
   In addition, the party's Central Committee Organization
Department said the party last year accepted only one out of four
applicants for membership in the elite group which rules China.
   The party took in 2 million new members last year out of 8
million applicants, bringing total membership to 47.75 million, the
official Xinhua News Agency said. About 1 billion people live in
China.
</TEXT>
