<HEAD>State Crackdown On Misuse Of Official Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe, (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government announced a crackdown
Friday on misuse of official cars and said civil servants caught
using them for personal business, such as to visit nightclubs or
liquor stores, will be disciplined.
   Justin Nyoka, secretary in the Minstry of National Supplies,
said teams will prowl the streets to track down the errant drivers.
   Cars with distinctive red and white government license plates
will be stopped at roadblocks to check if they are on ``legitimate
missions,'' Nyoka said. Offenders will face public service
misconduct charges.
   With about 80,000 civil servants, the government is the biggest
single employer in Zimbabwe and owns thousands of vehicles.
