<1ST_LINE>r p AM-Nunn-Veep     06-17 0319</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Nunn-Veep,310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nunn Says He Told Top Dukakis Aide He's Not Interested in Vice
Presidency</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVID PACE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. Sam Nunn said Friday he told Michael
Dukakis' campaign chairman this week he's not interested in the
vice presidential nomination.
   Nunn, D-Ga., didn't rule out accepting such an offer, saying in
an interview it would be ``very presumptuous'' to respond to
hypothetical questions about what he would do if the No. 2 spot
were offered by Dukakis, the likely Democratic presidential nominee.
   However, he said, ``It's not my desire to have that job offered
to me and then to turn it down. I don't think that's good for the
process'' or for Dukakis.
   Nunn was among the members of Congress who met individually this
week with Paul Brountas, Dukakis' campaign chairman, to discuss the
vice presidency.
   The Georgian, who is chairman of the Senate Armed Services
Committee, said he has talked with Dukakis at length on the
telephone in recent weeks about national security issues. But he
said the only time he has talked with the Massachusetts governor
about the vice presidency was when Dukakis told him Brountas would
be contacting him during his tour of Capitol Hill.
   Nunn said he got the impression from talking with Brountas that
Dukakis hasn't decided exactly what he is looking for in a vice
presidential nominee, either politically or in terms of what role
the vice president would play in his administration.
   Asked directly if he would accept a spot on the ticket if asked
by Dukakis, Nunn said, ``I think it's very presumptuous to sort of
set up a hypothetical example of what one would do if one were
offered something that one is not seeking and one is discouraging.''
   ``So I haven't gone to the extent of making a Sherman-like
statement. I feel it's kind of presumptuous and at this stage
unnecessary,'' he said.
</TEXT>
