<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BRF--UtahPoll     06-17 0130</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Utah Poll,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dukakis Gains In Utah Poll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALT LAKE CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic presidential candidate Michael
Dukakis is closing the gap on Republican George Bush in Utah, a
poll released Friday indicates.
   The Deseret News-KSL-TV poll found that 47 percent of those
polled favor Bush, while 38 percent prefer Dukakis.
   A similar poll two months ago found that 51 percent of those
questioned favored Bush and 36 percent favored Dukakis.
   The survey of 607 Utahns conducted May 31-June 1 has a margin of
error of 4 percent.
   Bush hopes President Reagan's popularity in western states will
help him carry the region this year. Reagan, who won his largest
pluralities of any state in Utah in 1980 and 1984, still has a job
approval rating of 69 percent here.
