<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Germany-Gold     06-17 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Germany-Gold,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Bandits Get $2 Million In Gold, Diamonds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two bandits, one wearing a cowboy
hat, stopped an armored truck and escaped with about $2 million
worth of gold, platinum and uncut diamonds, police reported Friday.
   They said the robbers struck just before midnight Thursday near
the Frankfurt airport and gave this account:
   The gunmen used a stolen car to block the route of the armored
truck. When the truck driver tried to swerve around the car, one
robber jumped onto the van, aimed a pistol at the two men inside
and ordered them to stop.
   The two robbers tied up the armored truck employees, loaded the
loot into the car and drove away. The driver and his assistant
called officials after freeing themselves.
   Police declined to say who owned the precious metal and diamonds
or give further information about the robbery.
</TEXT>
